Rhinocycler number 1. Stoked to have this one finished and ready to share @champstradeshows this week in Las Vegas. Put some hard work into this one, trying to use my best detail for function and art. This piece features my first 2 ever made dot stack marbles, and I love how they pop with these colors and shapes. This piece has a dual uptake where the water comes up and then drains back down the single drain tube. Function is on point. Rare photo of myself from a couple weeks ago at @champsglassgames @champstradeshows in Las Vegas. I decided to try and put myself out there more this year and compete in the games they have. It was a chance for me to try and curb some anxiety I have been having about blowing glass live or in other people's studio. I have worked alone in my garage for the past 15 years. 😅 
I was thrilled that I made my pieces in the allotted time, which was 3 hours. The piece pictured here was in the "Venetian" category. I managed to take first place in the competition, and it moved me forward to the glass master finals in February.  Huge thank you to my family and friends and my girlfriend for helping support me and encourage me to keep pushing through all the difficulties making and selling art for a living. Also, a huge thank you to all the artists at the show, making me feel welcomed and all making amazing art.  And not to forget a huge thanks to you all for following along and showing encouragement.  Much love! ❤️ 

#jellyfish#venetian##glassblowing#glassart#hardmanartglass#champs2023

Wanted to share this piece I made recently. When someone asked if I would make them a custom, he said the idea was an army tank. I was stoked to try it, but soon after, I was left in my thoughts trying to figure out a design or a way I could actually make a functional tank of decent size. It took me a while to come up with some ideas, and I almost decided that maybe it's not something I can make. Well, I stayed persistent and eventually came up with some 💡 This  functional tank is the outcome. I hope you guys like it! And thanks as always for supporting and following along the journey.
